Testing for drug impairment while driving is difficult due to the limitations of drug testing technology. There also is not an agreed-upon limit to determine impairment. The nationally recognized level of impairment for drunken driving is .08 g/mL blood alcohol concentration. But there is no similar national standard for other types of drugs such as marijuana.
